entry.def: If you say that something is so-so, you mean that it is average in quality, rather than being very good or very bad.

example.tran: 他们的午餐只能算是凑合。

example.ex: Sommers performed a flute solo a few weeks ago that got so-so reviews.
example.tran: 萨默斯几周前表演了一场长笛独奏，反映平平。
